				<h2>Synonym for photos.app to photos</h2>
<p>All of the newest questions in the <a href="https://apple.stackexchange.com/questions/tagged/photos" class="post-tag" title="show questions tagged &#39;photos&#39;" rel="tag">photos</a> tag refer to the new Apple Photos application. <a href="https://apple.stackexchange.com/questions/tagged/photos.app" class="post-tag" title="show questions tagged &#39;photos.app&#39;" rel="tag">photos.app</a> refers to the same thing. Could someone with enough reputation please make <a href="https://apple.stackexchange.com/questions/tagged/photos.app" class="post-tag" title="show questions tagged &#39;photos.app&#39;" rel="tag">photos.app</a> be a synonym of <a href="https://apple.stackexchange.com/questions/tagged/photos" class="post-tag" title="show questions tagged &#39;photos&#39;" rel="tag">photos</a> to group these together?</p>

<p>Admittedly, some older <a href="https://apple.stackexchange.com/questions/tagged/photos" class="post-tag" title="show questions tagged &#39;photos&#39;" rel="tag">photos</a> threads are about Aperture or iPhoto, but Apple is the one to have introduced the confusing naming, and Apple Photos does represent the successor application.</p>

