				<p><p>From the <a href="https://apple.stackexchange.com/tags">tags page</a>:</p>

<blockquote>
  <p><strong>photos</strong> x 590</p>
  
  <p>Photographs and photography</p>
</blockquote>

<p>And:</p>

<blockquote>
  <p><strong>photos.app</strong> x 81</p>
  
  <p>The Apple photo manager and editor and successor to iPhoto and Aperture. Introduced in 2015.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Making <strong>photos</strong> a synonym of <strong>photos.app</strong> has the potential to mis-tag 590 questions now. Questions that pre-date the existence of the Photos app from Apple and have nothing to do with the tool.</p>

<p>Our convention has been to use <code>.app</code> on tags to denote the Apple product with the noun.</p>

<p>Violating this convention in this particular case does not, in my opinion, sound like a good idea.</p>
</p><br>
